Uh, I'm flying this plane today.
First complaint: We need cute flight logs. Black is too boring, and pink isn't even pink but salmon-colored.
I've wanted to fly since I was young.
Today my dream came true... I flew a plane today. I'm still in shock.
Flightaware data.
Saturday I was planning to try again. The weather looks not so good now, but it's only Monday today.
It seems that the challenge on this aspect has just begun. Due to FAA's stance on certain drugs, I may have a hard time getting qualified for a physical exam.
This isn't impossible, but it will take a lot of time and require a lot of extra work.
Although this is a bit disappointing, it's just another problem to be solved, and it looks like it's definitely solvable at this point. It just requires a lot of time and money.
If you want to know what challenges I'll be facing next：
FAA doesn't like ADHD. If you are taking medication for ADHD, you definitely won't get a qualified medical certificate.
https://youtu.be/W5JSfq6LLAU?si=xIxPaY8ayqqNSj4c
If I have the chance to customize the tail number of the plane in the future, it must be a variation of N1337_, where _ represents any available letter character.
Of course, the sun would still rise as usual when I'm not around, haha. What a letdown.
I have to fly again, but this awful weather is really not cooperating.
Welcome to the world of general aviation! 😜
Based on the ads I see on YouTube, the recommended videos I see and the comments I see, I feel that the airline industry tends to be conservative in tracking.
If the weather allows, I will fly again on Saturday.
